~Report on the Results of the Project~ Conclusion:
Project LUNA, the plan to manifest the deceased,
has failed. The plan will be immediately
terminated and funding will be frozen. The planner
of the project, Luna Hisube, will be dismissed
from the board of directors.

The power supply to the underground research
facility, as well as the Subterranean Boundary
Device and the Manifestation Device, used in the
project shall be completely halted within 5 days
from the date of this directive. Afterward, all
access routes to the underground facility shall be
completely sealed off.

Furthermore, with the suspension of the project,
the Hikou Group has announced its withdrawal from
the Sakuhai City urban development project. As for
future business operations, they will be
transferred to subsidiary companies, but the
specific transfer destination will be notified at
a later date.

The Unexpected Effects of the Manifestation Device
- The manifestation device interferes with the
universal unconscious realm, allowing access to
submerged consciousness or souls.

In Jungian psychology, where does the shadow
exist? According to one theory, there is a paper
that suggests it exists in the realm of the
collective unconscious.

The cause of the frequent malfunctions that have
been occurring since the start of the plan is
believed to be none other than this shadow itself.
A beacon is used for supplementary purposes, but
it is merely a device for supplementation.

Connecting to the universal unconscious realm,
which was an unknown territory, could it also lead
to connecting with shadows other than the target?
There are too many individuals clearly
experiencing mental abnormalities. Seasonal
affective disorder is believed to be the cause,
but it doesn't seem so.
Actor03

\n<\N[3]>Accessing the soul... I never thought something
like this would be possible...

~Speculation on the Collective Hallucination
Symptoms~ Since the start of the project, there
have been numerous reports of hallucinations and
visions among the personnel in the underground
facility. Here are several hypotheses that have
been compiled.

The three interesting examples of symptoms are as
follows: 1. Seeing an acquaintance who should be
deceased. 2. Seeing a family member who should be
at home. 3. Seeing a person who should have passed
away, even though they have never met before.

These are reports of witnessing people who should
not be present at the scene, hearing their voices,
and even having conversations with them. The
credibility is considered high because the
information obtained through hallucinations
includes details that the individuals themselves
should not have known, as confirmed by third
parties.

From the beginning, the apparition device was a
device that connected to the imperceptible realm,
the universal unconscious realm, and it was
unknown what kind of impact it would have by
coming into contact with memories and
consciousness that exist beyond.

If we were to say that those are the shadows that
Jung speaks of, then it would make sense. However,
it may be premature to come to that conclusion. If
that is the case, could it be that the death
spirits and life spirits that have been passed
down in Japan since ancient times were referring
to those beings?
Actor03

\n<\N[3]>Death spirits...life spirits...are there others
like them as well...
A
